Description: 21 fragments of Coptic codex page. Twelve frames (EA 76565-76) are stored together in an archival box.
Curator's comments: EA 76415 may belong to the same group.

Previously unregistered material stored in Papyrus Store. The frame labelled 'No 4'. A label stuck to the glass reads '3101 Hartw[ell] Museum. Unrolled by Mr Lee and Mr Bonomi'. A label inside the frame reads '280'.
Acquisition notes: 'Gift of papyri from Hartwell House by Messrs Rutter and Marchant.'
